cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of hyperspectral image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and spatial feature fusion. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of artificial neural networks (ANNs) and centerloss also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also involves image retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with hyperspectral images.
